      "span_text": "The balance of payments constrained growth model that owes its origins to  takes a demand-induced view of growth.  introduced a simple analytical model to show that a country's long-run rate of economic growth will be limited by its foreign trade performance, that is, by the size of the income elasticity of its imports relative to the pace of expansion of its exports.",
